President Trump and Tim Cook, CEO of Apple, attended the opening ceremony of a new Mac Pro manufacturing plant in Austin, Texas. President Trump praised Apple for building plants in the United States and expressed his admiration for Tim Cook. Cook announced a one-billion-dollar investment for a three-million-square-foot site in Austin, emphasizing the importance of the city for Apple's future. President Trump also spoke about the impeachment inquiry, calling it a hoax and criticizing the media for being dishonest. He defended his conversation with the President of Ukraine and accused the whistleblower of being a political operative. The President also discussed the possibility of exempting Apple from China tariffs and his belief that the U.S. has a stronger economy than China.